  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed operating points. Thirteen credibility factors were assessed; twelve meet or exceed their required levels. One factor — Model Form — carries a structured level shortfall (achievedLevel 2, requiredLevel 3) that the decision rationale addresses through expert-judgment bridging arguments. The package decision is Accepted on the basis of the aggregate evidence body.",
